<!--
GOAL file template for `dvx watch`.

How to use:
1. Copy this file to <todo-dir>/GOAL-<short-slug>.md (default todo dir: .dvx/todo).
   The filename becomes the working branch name: GOAL-add-rate-limit.md -> branch goal-add-rate-limit.
   Use only lowercase letters, digits, and dashes in the slug, and pick a slug whose
   goal-<slug> branch does not already exist — otherwise the watcher skips the goal as failed.
2. Fill in every section below. Delete this comment block and any section that is
   genuinely empty.
3. Drop the file into the todo directory while `dvx watch` is running (or start
   `dvx watch` afterwards). Outside of MERGE requests, the watcher processes
   files oldest-first by file modification time, then filename.

What the implementer session is (write the goal for THIS audience):
- This file is handed to a single headless Claude Code session using the
  configured model (default: `claude-opus-4-8`): the watcher snapshots it to
  .dvx/watch/current-goal.md and starts the session with
  the built-in /goal command pointing at that snapshot (the /goal condition has
  a 4000-character cap, so file contents are never passed inline). The goal is
  checked before the session may stop — so write requirements as outcomes that
  check can verify. This file is all the instruction and context the implementer
  receives; it cannot see the conversation that produced it. There is no length
  limit on this file.
- The session is non-interactive. Nobody can answer questions, so this file must
  pre-answer every decision. Anything left ambiguous will be decided by the
  implementer alone.
- The session runs at the repository root on a fresh branch (goal-<slug>) cut from
  the branch `dvx watch` was started on. After the session, the watcher deletes this
  goal file, commits any remaining changes in logical groups, merges the branch back
  with --no-ff, deletes it, and pushes the watch branch to its remote. Do not ask
  the implementer to push, open PRs, or merge — the watcher owns integration.
- The session has a 4-hour timeout. Scope the goal to comfortably fit; split larger
  work into multiple GOAL files (they run sequentially, each on its own branch).
-->

# Goal: <one-line imperative statement of the outcome>

## Why

<1-3 sentences: the problem being solved and the value of solving it. This drives
the implementer's judgment calls and commit messages.>

## Current state

<What exists today that the implementer must know before touching anything.
Be concrete — name files, functions, and behaviors:>

- `path/to/relevant/file.py` — <what it does and how it relates to this goal>
- `path/to/tests/test_file.py` — <existing test coverage>
- <Known quirks, in-flight work, or landmines in this area>

## Requirements

<Numbered, individually verifiable. "Add X to Y" not "improve Y".>

1. <Requirement>
2. <Requirement>
3. <Requirement>

## Out of scope

<Explicitly fence off adjacent work the implementer might be tempted to do:
refactors, renames, doc updates, dependency upgrades, etc.>

- <Non-goal>

## Decisions already made

<Pre-answer every choice so the implementer never has to guess. Include the why
when it affects implementation.>

- <Decision>: <choice> — <rationale>
- For any decision NOT listed here: choose the reversible, lowest-risk option,
  note it in a code comment or commit message, and continue. Do not stop to ask.

## Verification

<Exact commands that must pass before the work is done. The implementer runs
these itself — include any setup needed (venv activation, env vars, etc.).>

```bash
<command to run the test suite, e.g.: cd dvx && uv run pytest>
<command to run the linter, e.g.: cd dvx && uv run ruff check src tests>
```

- New behavior must be covered by new or updated tests, not just existing ones.
- All commands above must exit 0. If a failure cannot be fixed within this goal's
  scope, fix the code you changed — never weaken, skip, or delete existing tests
  to get to green.

## Rules for the implementer (do not edit this section)

- Work only on the current branch. Do NOT push, open pull requests, switch
  branches, or merge — the watcher handles integration.
- Do NOT create, modify, or delete anything under the todo directory (default
  `.dvx/todo/`) or `.dvx/`. The watcher fails the goal if commits touch these paths
  or if queued GOAL-*.md files change during the session.
- Committing is optional: a follow-up session commits remaining changes in logical
  groups. If you do commit, exclude the todo directory and `.dvx/`, and explain
  why in the message, not what.
- Leave the working tree in a state where everything you changed can be committed:
  no stray scratch files, debug output, or half-applied edits.
- Never ask questions — there is no one to answer. Apply the decisions above; for
  anything else, take the reversible default and keep going.
- If the goal is truly impossible as written (missing dependency, contradictory
  requirements), make no speculative changes, state clearly in your final message
  what blocked you and what is needed, and exit; failing loudly beats guessing.
